==Description==

The [[FreeGrid_StorageGrid|FreeGrid StorageGrid]] tool creates a storage grid.

This tool is part of the [[FreeGrid_Workbench|FreeGrid Workbench]], an [https://www.freecad.org/addons.php external workbench] that can be installed with the [[Image:Std_AddonMgr.svg|24px]] [[Std_AddonMgr|Addon Manager]].

==Usage==

# There are several ways to invoke the tool:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:FreeGrid_StorageGrid.svg|16px]] [[FreeGrid_StorageGrid|Storage grid]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|FreeGrid → [[Image:FreeGrid_StorageGrid.svg|16px]] Storage grid}} option from the menu.
# A storage grid is created with properties based on the current preferences.
# Optionally select the object and change its properties in the [[Property_editor|Property editor]].

==Properties==

A FreeGrid StorageBox object is derived from a [[Part_Feature|Part Feature]] object and inherits all its properties. It also has the following additional properties:

===Data===

{{Properties_Title|Grid features}}

* {{PropertyData|Corner Connectors|Bool}}: Default is {{TRUE}}. Add cavities for corner connectors.
* {{PropertyData|Extra Bottom Material|Length}}: Default is {{Value|16 mm}}. Extra thickness under the grid.
* {{PropertyData|Is Subtractive|Bool}}: Default is {{FALSE}}. Create a grid suitable for subtractive manufacturing.

{{Properties_Title|Magnet mount}}

* {{PropertyData|Include Magnets|Bool}}: Default is {{TRUE}}. Include magnet receptacles.
* {{PropertyData|Magnet Diameter|Length}}: Default is {{Value|6 mm}}. Diameter of the magnets.
* {{PropertyData|Magnet Height|Length}}: Default is {{Value|2 mm}}. Height of the magnets.

{{Properties_Title|Size}}

* {{PropertyData|Depth|IntegerConstraint}}: Default is {{Value|2}}. Number of 50 mm units in the Y direction of the object.
* {{PropertyData|Width|IntegerConstraint}}: Default is {{Value|3}}. Number of 50 mm units in the X direction of the object.


